Description: Corroded iron leaf-shaped and tanged arrow-head, with flat rhomboid cross-section and longitudinal mid-rib on both sides.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 78 § 77, p. 110, pl. xxxvii, 14)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.69, fig.2, p.183, pl.25)
